    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-07-24T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-07-24T19:00:00-05:00" n="435"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d435">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">974.531/7–2251: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Egypt</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d435fn1">Drafted by Messrs. <persName corresp="#p_SW1"
                            >Stabler</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_JGL1">G. L.
                            Jones</persName> and signed for the Secretary by Mr. <persName
                            corresp="#p_MGC2">McGhee</persName>. Repeated to London, Paris, Tel
                        Aviv, and New York; sent by air to Jidda, Baghdad, Ankara, Damascus, Beirut,
                        and Amman.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-07-24T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 24, 1951—8 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>116. For <gloss target="#t_Amb1">Amb</gloss> from <persName corresp="#p_MGC2"
                        >McGhee</persName>. Wld it help you re <gloss target="#t_Deptel1"
                        >Deptel</gloss> 87 Jul 19<note n="2" xml:id="d435fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_781">p. 781</ref>.</note>
                        (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 88 Jul 22)<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d435fn3">See footnote 4, <ref target="#pg_782">p. 782</ref>.</note>
                    if I were to put raising restrictions to Egpyt Counselor here (<gloss
                        target="#t_Amb1">Amb</gloss> unfortunately absent on West Coast) on basis
                    friends of Egypt recall Egypt’s high role in formation <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                        >UN</gloss> and dislike prospect Egypt being hailed before <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> for restrictions which <hi rend="italic">a</hi>)
                    Do little if any harm to Israel; <hi rend="italic">b</hi>.) Exacerbate
                    Anglo-Egypt relations; <hi rend="italic">c</hi>) Have resulted protest most
                    maritime powers; and, <hi rend="italic">d</hi>) Contribute to instability in
                        area?<note n="4" xml:id="d435fn4">In telegram 106 July 26, not printed,
                        Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Caffery</persName> answered this
                        question in the affirmative (974.531/7–2651).</note>
                </p>
                <p>I might make pt that Egypt’s voluntary compliance with spirit of <persName
                        corresp="#p_RWE1">Riley</persName>’s special comite decision before pressed
                    to do so by <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> wld serve <pb facs="0837" n="797"
                        xml:id="pg_797"/> as model to world including Israel of proper <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> spirit and wld win Egypt internatl acclaim.<note
                        n="5" xml:id="d435fn5">On July 25, Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_CJ1"
                            >Caffery</persName> reported that <persName corresp="#p_SBM1"
                            >Salaheddin</persName> had again expressed the hope that means would be
                        found to end the Suez restrictions controversy without bringing it to the
                        Security Council. <persName corresp="#p_SBM1">Salaheddin</persName> stated
                        that the United States, and only the United States, could take effective and
                        pertinent action if it desired to do so. <persName corresp="#p_CJ1"
                            >Caffery</persName> reiterated to <persName corresp="#p_SBM1"
                            >Salaheddin</persName> that the only means to accomplish this would be
                        to abolish the restrictions. The latter again replied that Egypt could
                        alleviate restrictions considerably but could not abolish them. (Telegram
                        98, not printed, 974.531/7–2551)</note> [<persName corresp="#p_MGC2"
                        >McGhee</persName>.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
